  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A fast track recovery program (thoracic epidural anesthesia, carbohydrate drink preoperative,
      early removal of chest tubes) is evaluated compared to conventional perioperative treatment
      (patient controlled analgesia, no carbohydrate drink preoperative) in patients with FEV1 &lt;
      70% of expected value or &lt; 1.5L who undergo resections of the lung.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
